minikube start

Per creare configmaps da file di config:

kubectl create configmap <nome> --from-file=<pathToFile>

Per vedere il contenuto della configmap

kubectl describe cm <nome>

-----------------

apiVersion: rabbitmq.com/v1beta1
kind: RabbitmqCluster
metadata:
  name: definition

THis is the part required ofr rabbitmq, everything else is configuration
https://www.rabbitmq.com/kubernetes/operator/using-operator.html#create

kubectl get deployment -n <namespace> (rabbitmq-system)

see everything: 
   kubectl get all -n rabbitmq-system -l app.kubernetes.io/name=rabbitmq-idca-deployment

get into the pod:
  kubectl -n rabbitmq-system exec --stdin --tty pod/rabbitmq-idca-deployment-server-0 -- /bin/bash

to see enabled plugins
  rabbitmq-plugins list 

create configmap for deifnitions
minikube kubectl -- create configmap definitions --from-file='def.json=k8s/definitions.json'
